file.name: azure.com-sql-importExport-2014-04-01-swagger.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.0
info:
  description: Provides create and read functionality for Import/Export operations on Azure
    SQL databases.
  title: Azure SQL Database Import/Export spec
  version: 2014-04-01
  x-apisguru-categories:
    - cloud
  x-logo:
    url: https://assets.onestore.ms/cdnfiles/onestorerolling-1606-01000/shell/v3/images/logo/microsoft.png
  x-origin:
    - format: swagger
      url: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Azure/azure-rest-api-specs/master/specification/sql/resource-manager/Microsoft.Sql/stable/2014-04-01/importExport.json
      version: "2.0"
  x-providerName: azure.com
  x-serviceName: sql-importExport
  x-tags:
    - Azure
    - Microsoft
paths:
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/servers/{serverName}/databases/{databaseName}/export":
    post:
      description: Exports a database to a bacpac.
      operationId: Databases_Export
      parameters:
        - description: The API version to use for the request.
          in: query
          name: api-version
          required: true
          x-ms-parameter-location: client
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            Export a database into a new bacpac file with SAS key:
              value: 2014-04-01
            Export a database into a new bacpac file with storage key:
              value: 2014-04-01
        - description: The subscription ID that identifies an Azure subscription.
          in: path
          name: subscriptionId
          required: true
          x-ms-parameter-location: client
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            Export a database into a new bacpac file with SAS key:
              value: 00000000-1111-2222-3333-444444444444
            Export a database into a new bacpac file with storage key:
              value: 00000000-1111-2222-3333-444444444444
        - description: The name of the resource group that contains the resource. You can
            obtain this value from the Azure Resource Manager API or the portal.
          in: path
          name: resourceGroupName
          required: true
          x-ms-parameter-location: method
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            Export a database into a new bacpac file with SAS key:
              value: sqlcrudtest-4799
            Export a database into a new bacpac file with storage key:
              value: sqlcrudtest-4799
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ServerNameParameter"
        - description: The name of the database to be exported.
          in: path
          name: databaseName
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            Export a database into a new bacpac file with SAS key:
              value: testdb
            Export a database into a new bacpac file with storage key:
              value: testdb
      requestBody:
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: "#/components/schemas/ExportRequest"
        description: The required parameters for exporting a database.
        required: true
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/ImportExportResponse"
              examples:
                Export a database into a new bacpac file with SAS key:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/Export_a_database_into_a_new_bacpac_\
                    file_with_SAS_key"
                Export a database into a new bacpac file with storage key:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/Export_a_database_into_a_new_bacpac_\
                    file_with_storage_key"
        "202":
          description: Accepted
      tags:
        - ImportExport
      x-ms-long-running-operation: true
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/servers/{serverName}/databases/{databaseName}/extensions/{extensionName}":
    put:
      description: Creates an import operation that imports a bacpac into an existing
        database. The existing database must be empty.
      operationId: Databases_CreateImportOperation
      parameters:
        - description: The API version to use for the request.
          in: query
          name: api-version
          required: true
          x-ms-parameter-location: client
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            Import bacpac into an existing database Max with SAS key:
              value: 2014-04-01
            Import bacpac into an existing database Max with storage key:
              value: 2014-04-01
            Import bacpac into an existing database Min with SAS key:
              value: 2014-04-01
            Import bacpac into an existing database Min with storage key:
              value: 2014-04-01
        - description: The subscription ID that identifies an Azure subscription.
          in: path
          name: subscriptionId
          required: true
          x-ms-parameter-location: client
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            Import bacpac into an existing database Max with SAS key:
              value: 00000000-1111-2222-3333-444444444444
            Import bacpac into an existing database Max with storage key:
              value: 00000000-1111-2222-3333-444444444444
            Import bacpac into an existing database Min with SAS key:
              value: 00000000-1111-2222-3333-444444444444
            Import bacpac into an existing database Min with storage key:
              value: 00000000-1111-2222-3333-444444444444
        - description: The name of the resource group that contains the resource. You can
            obtain this value from the Azure Resource Manager API or the portal.
          in: path
          name: resourceGroupName
          required: true
          x-ms-parameter-location: method
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            Import bacpac into an existing database Max with SAS key:
              value: sqlcrudtest-4799
            Import bacpac into an existing database Max with storage key:
              value: sqlcrudtest-4799
            Import bacpac into an existing database Min with SAS key:
              value: sqlcrudtest-4799
            Import bacpac into an existing database Min with storage key:
              value: sqlcrudtest-4799
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ServerNameParameter"
        - description: The name of the database to import into
          in: path
          name: databaseName
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            Import bacpac into an existing database Max with SAS key:
              value: testdb
            Import bacpac into an existing database Max with storage key:
              value: testdb
            Import bacpac into an existing database Min with SAS key:
              value: testdb
            Import bacpac into an existing database Min with storage key:
              value: testdb
        - description: The name of the operation to perform
          in: path
          name: extensionName
          required: true
          x-ms-enum:
            modelAsString: true
            name: ExtensionName
          schema:
            type: string
            enum:
              - import
          examples:
            Import bacpac into an existing database Max with SAS key:
              value: import
            Import bacpac into an existing database Max with storage key:
              value: import
            Import bacpac into an existing database Min with SAS key:
              value: import
            Import bacpac into an existing database Min with storage key:
              value: import
      requestBody:
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: "#/components/schemas/ImportExtensionRequest"
        description: The required parameters for importing a Bacpac into a database.
        required: true
      responses:
        "201":
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/ImportExportResponse"
              examples:
                Import bacpac into an existing database Max with SAS key:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/Import_bacpac_into_an_existing_datab\
                    ase_Max_with_SAS_key"
                Import bacpac into an existing database Max with storage key:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/Import_bacpac_into_an_existing_datab\
                    ase_Max_with_storage_key"
                Import bacpac into an existing database Min with SAS key:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/Import_bacpac_into_an_existing_datab\
                    ase_Min_with_SAS_key"
                Import bacpac into an existing database Min with storage key:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/Import_bacpac_into_an_existing_datab\
                    ase_Min_with_storage_key"
        "202":
          description: Accepted
      tags:
        - ImportExport
      x-ms-long-running-operation: true
  "/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/servers/{serverName}/import":
    post:
      description: "Imports a bacpac into a new database. "
      operationId: Databases_Import
      parameters:
        - description: The API version to use for the request.
          in: query
          name: api-version
          required: true
          x-ms-parameter-location: client
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            Import bacpac into new database Max with SAS key:
              value: 2014-04-01
            Import bacpac into new database Max with storage key:
              value: 2014-04-01
            Import bacpac into new database Min with SAS key:
              value: 2014-04-01
            Import bacpac into new database Min with storage key:
              value: 2014-04-01
        - description: The subscription ID that identifies an Azure subscription.
          in: path
          name: subscriptionId
          required: true
          x-ms-parameter-location: client
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            Import bacpac into new database Max with SAS key:
              value: 00000000-1111-2222-3333-444444444444
            Import bacpac into new database Max with storage key:
              value: 00000000-1111-2222-3333-444444444444
            Import bacpac into new database Min with SAS key:
              value: 00000000-1111-2222-3333-444444444444
            Import bacpac into new database Min with storage key:
              value: 00000000-1111-2222-3333-444444444444
        - description: The name of the resource group that contains the resource. You can
            obtain this value from the Azure Resource Manager API or the portal.
          in: path
          name: resourceGroupName
          required: true
          x-ms-parameter-location: method
          schema:
            type: string
          examples:
            Import bacpac into new database Max with SAS key:
              value: sqlcrudtest-4799
            Import bacpac into new database Max with storage key:
              value: sqlcrudtest-4799
            Import bacpac into new database Min with SAS key:
              value: sqlcrudtest-4799
            Import bacpac into new database Min with storage key:
              value: sqlcrudtest-4799
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/ServerNameParameter"
      requestBody:
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: "#/components/schemas/ImportRequest"
        description: The required parameters for importing a Bacpac into a database.
        required: true
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/ImportExportResponse"
              examples:
                Import bacpac into new database Max with SAS key:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/Import_bacpac_into_new_database_Max_\
                    with_SAS_key"
                Import bacpac into new database Max with storage key:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/Import_bacpac_into_new_database_Max_\
                    with_storage_key"
                Import bacpac into new database Min with SAS key:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/Import_bacpac_into_new_database_Min_\
                    with_SAS_key"
                Import bacpac into new database Min with storage key:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/Import_bacpac_into_new_database_Min_\
                    with_storage_key"
        "202":
          description: Accepted
      tags:
        - ImportExport
      x-ms-long-running-operation: true

          enum:
            - Import

            name: ImportOperationMode

      properties:
        name:
          description: The name of the extension.
          type: string
        properties:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/ImportExtensionProperties"
        type:
          description: The type of the extension.
          type: string
    ImportRequest:
      allOf:
        - $ref: "#/components/schemas/ExportRequest"
      description: Import database parameters.
      properties:
        databaseName:
          description: The name of the database to import.
          type: string
        edition:
          description: "The edition for the database being created.\r

            \r

            The list of SKUs may vary by region and support offer.
            To determine the SKUs (including the SKU name, tier/edition, family,
            and capacity) that are available to your subscription in an Azure
            region, use the `Capabilities_ListByLocation` REST API or one of the
            following commands:\r

            \r

            ```azurecli\r

            az sql db list-editions -l <location> -o table\r

            ````\r

            \r

            ```powershell\r

            Get-AzSqlServerServiceObjective -Location <location>\r

            ````\r\n"
          enum:
            - Web
            - Business
            - Basic
            - Standard
            - Premium
            - PremiumRS
            - Free
            - Stretch
            - DataWarehouse
            - System
            - System2
            - GeneralPurpose
            - BusinessCritical
            - Hyperscale
          type: string
          x-ms-enum:
            modelAsString: true
